character.name: Frank Castle
character.description:
Frank Castle rides the bus. He didn't always, but now he does. He's back on the bus for a few years now, and once he gets off the bus he'll be back on it again someday. There's always the bus. Everyday, other bus riders see this grizzled old ex-Marine with classic Semper-Fi and UCAS Marine Corp unit tattoos. Another senior citizen staring off into AR while on their way to the wage slavery of the moment. Despair and resignation are quiet. Frank likes quiet.
Caslte lives in an apartment building out in Renton, which was converted from a 20th century bank, from back when people cared about stuff more than bits and bytes. Its a cramped unit with with one window that overlooks Lake Washington and Mercer Island... but you can only see it from the top of the chinup bar he installed in the windowframe. The rest of the place contains a basic computer, a murphy bed, and the most comfortable chair he's ever known. And he knows from chairs. He's always on the lookout for chairs being discarded, or at thrift shops. He has an uncanny ability to fall instantly asleep in this particular chair, and often sleeps upright when he's too tired to pull down his murphy bed.
Renton is a rough neighborhood. He's got a variety of knives and pistols hidden about the place.
He managed to talk the landlord into leasing him the vault in addition to his unit. He has removed all safe deposit boxes from the vault and uses it as a miniature safe house. While his apartment is spartan and free of distraction, this vault is full of half full weapons racks, ammunition cases, and his library. Actual goddamn books made of goddamn paper. Maps too. Paper ones.
The vault works. It has no electricity, and no data lines. Its density makes it a natural faraday cage. But it works, and watching those bolts drive into the wall is the most satisfying part of his return from each run, successful or not.
There is a cot in here, a table and a few chairs. He saved the comfy one for his apartment. He comes down here to think, to plan, and sometimes just to zone out while tooling on his weapons. He has a small but well rounded machinists setup, including a lathe, a mill, and a few other odds and ends. Enough to keep his weapons well tuned, repair them, and make minor modifications to them.
character.background:
Ex- UCAS Marine Captain. Learned Parkour from the Spiders. Lost his family and doesn't want to talk about it. Has a long lost daughter somewhere, though he's honestly not sure if she's alive or not. He searches for her periodically, but has resigned himself to the fact that 30 years is a long time to be missing. Once in a while something gives him hope, but the search always quickly ends.
Frank has been running the Shadows for quite some time, and he's had some ups and downs. Some years he ends up ahead, most years he ends up in the hole. After a good year, he can put that bus pass away, but he never loses track of it. He's lost money and he's lost men; this isn't the first team of runners he's worked with. He's learned a lot from all of them.
character.concept: Like Cable meets Hannibal from the A-Team. Very perceptive, and has a constant situational calculus running in the back of his head. Those equations only have 2 answers: Fight or Flight. Castle is at his best when surrounded with a good team, because his leadership can make them a great team.
